channel.title: Obfuscator? Some problems
channel.description:
Does anyone know of a free obfuscator that actually works? I've tried all of the popular ones such a ProGuard, yGuard, JavaGuard and none of them seem to be working for me at all. They either give me errors when attempting to obfuscate, or they don't obfuscate the output at all.
I tried an evaluation version of a paid obfuscator called DashO, and it seems to work fine, all my classes were obfuscated and I was able to run the jar file, however some features didn't work, does anyone know why?
Are there any out there that work?

item.title: Obfuscator? Some problems
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

I use proguard4.8 just fine. Are you sure you are setting it up correctly? The only settings that I had to put in are the input.jar and output.jar, along with the class to keep. It does the rest.
